The #Dow could still go up to top at a much higher price. I love numbers, so this is right up my allley. Based on my interpretation of past cycles, I think it could top out around 44,000. Around 2011, I was thinking 30,000, but I reassessed it.

There was a recession from Oct 1926 to Nov 1927, which was a few years before 1929 top. The economy had a bounce after the recession and unemployment dropped and the #Dow doubled from 1927-1929. Even with the recession, Dow was up over 14% from Oct 1, 1926 to Nov 1, 1927. Weird.
